en_768040_0	At least 23 people were killed in Peru after a bus travelling along a twisting mountain fell into a ravine.
en_768040_1	The accident occurred at about 0300 on a road between Cusco and Puerto Maldonado.
en_768040_2	The bus then plummeted off the road into the ravine, which according to reports is more than 100 metres deep.
en_768040_3	Reports on the number of passengers on board vary but at least 50 people were on the bus.
en_768040_4	Dozens of passengers were injured and transported to hospital.
en_768040_5	Police are investigating the cause of the crash.
en_768040_6	Bus accidents are common in Peru, where vehicle and highway maintenance is poor and roads snake along precarious mountains.
